&gt; How about this for a character entrance?
&gt;
&gt; ::DeathScythe::
&gt;
&gt; &quot;And you were sent here to eliminate us?&quot;
&gt;
&gt; DeathScythe turns his head to look at the Maximal captain, his eyes never
&gt; leaving the other two Maximals in the room.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Yes,&quot; he says quietly, his voice sounding like death, &quot;I am offering you
a
&gt; chance to live. Simply give me what I want.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; The Maximal captain shakes his head. &quot;Us Maximals don&#39;t give in to that. I
&gt; suggest you retreat. You&#39;re outnumbered three to one.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Then you die,&quot; DeathScythe says, his voice no more than a whisper.
&gt;
&gt; Several seconds pass, feeling like hours to the four bots.
&gt;
&gt; Without warning, DeathScythe jumps forward, his fist slamming into the
head
&gt; of one of the Maximals, knocking him unconscious. The other two jump at
him,
&gt; DeathScythe ducking, the other two slamming into each other. With an
upward
&gt; punch, he sends the Maximals flying into opposite sides of the room.
&gt;
&gt; The captain stands up, the other Maximal obvioustly knocked unconscious.
&gt; DeathScythe grins.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;So... The heroic Maximals try a three on one battle. How pathetic!&quot;
&gt; DeathScythe&#39;s grin broadens, the assassin reaching behind him. The Maximal
&gt; commander jumps forward, swinging a fist at DeathScythe.
&gt;
&gt; DeathScythe sidesteps, the hand behind his back producing a dagger, which
he
&gt; stabs downward into the Maximal&#39;s neck. The captain&#39;s eyes widen, his body
&gt; flying into a comp console, the console exploding.
&gt;
&gt; The ship that they were all in goes into a spin, dipping down toward a
blue
&gt; planet. DeathScythe is thrown against the wall, going unconscious.
&gt; ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
&gt; The impact as the ship hits down in Africa is tremendous. The systems of
the
&gt; ship blink out, the DNA replicator the only one left online, but barely.
&gt; ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
&gt; DeathScythe opens his eyes.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;I see you&#39;re awake.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; The assassin looks over at the source of the voice, his eyes widening. The
&gt; bot standing in front of him was the Maximal captain, holding his own head
in
&gt; his arms.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;I&#39;ve been waiting for you to wake up,&quot; says the captain&#39;s head.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;W-w-w-w-w-w,&quot; DeathScythe mumbles, trying to form words, &quot;W-what happened
to
&gt; your head?&quot;
&gt;
&gt; &quot;My head?&quot; the head frowns, then suddenly opens its mouth, &quot;Oh! My head!
Oh,
&gt; you knocked it off in that fight.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; DeathScythe shakes his head. &quot;No I didn&#39;t, I stabbed you in the neck with
a
&gt; dagger.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Are you sure?&quot;
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Yes.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; The head frowns, &quot;Oh, you must be right.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; The captain lifts his head to his shoulders, the wound healing. He then
takes
&gt; out a dagger and stabs it into his own neck. &quot;That better?&quot;
&gt;
&gt; Eyes widened in astonishment, DeathScythe nods.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Good. Follow me.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; Silently, DeathScythe stands up, walking after the Maximal captain. The
&gt; hallway they were walking down looked strange, circular, and dripping with
&gt; something.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Where are we?&quot;
&gt;
&gt; &quot;In me.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; &quot;What??&quot; DeathScythe stops, looking at the Maximal.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;In me,&quot; the captain says patiently, &quot;I think we&#39;re in my abdomen.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; &quot;No we&#39;re not. You&#39;re right there. I can&#39;t be inside you.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Sure you can, just shut up and follow.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; DeathScythe growls. This Maximal was pissing him off. The assassin swings
his
&gt; fist at the Maximals&#39;s head.
&gt;
&gt; The fist passes through the head, the Maximal turning around.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;That was rude,&quot; he says simply.
&gt;
&gt; DeathScythe blinks. He had been expecting the Maximal to get hit and fall
&gt; unconscious. &quot;What was?&quot;
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Pointing that spoon at me.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; &quot;What spoon?&quot;
&gt;
&gt; &quot;The one in your left hand.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; DeathScythe looks down at his left hand, surprised to see a small silver
&gt; spoon in it.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Um........&quot; he says, continuing to follow the Maximal. He was now
completely
&gt; confused, &quot;Are you sure we&#39;re inside you?&quot;
&gt;
&gt; The Maximal turns around with an annoyed look on his face, &quot;Look, this is
my
&gt; dream, and whatever I say goes!&quot;
&gt;
&gt; DeathScythe&#39;s mouth opens, trying to say something, but to confused to
decide
&gt; what to say. &quot;Your dream?!&quot; he finally blurts out, &quot;If this is a dream,
it&#39;s
&gt; my dream!&quot;
&gt;
&gt; DeathScythe lifts his left hand, about to throw the spoon at the Maximal,
&gt; when he discoveres the spoon missing.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;YOU STOLE IT!&quot; he yells at the Maximal.
&gt;
&gt; The Maximal captain turns around, &quot;Stole what?&quot;
&gt;
&gt; &quot;The spoon I had in my hand!&quot; yells an enraged DeathScythe.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;You didn&#39;t,&quot; the captain says calmly.
&gt;
&gt; DeathScythe blinks. &quot;Didn&#39;t what?&quot;
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Have a spoon in your hand.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; &quot;I did?&quot;
&gt;
&gt; &quot;No.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Oh,&quot; DeathStorm says, blinking a few times to get his thoughts in order,
but
&gt; to no avail. DeathStorm finally cracks, losing his temper, he lets out an
&gt; insane yell. &quot;ENOUGH!!!&quot; DeathScythe yells, reaching for his gun.
&gt;
&gt; He blinks as he looks down at what he though was the gun, suddenly
realizing
&gt; that it was a bot&#39;s arm.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Wha-who-who-wh-what is this?&quot; he asks, his eyes wide.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;It&#39;s an arm.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; &quot;I KNOW IT&#39;S AN ARM, YOU DIMWIT,&quot; DeathScythe yells on the top of his,
&quot;BUT
&gt; WHOSE SLAGGIN&#39; ARM IS THIS?!!!!&quot;
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Mine,&quot; the Maximal says calmly, turning around, &quot;Can I have it back?&quot;
&gt;
&gt; DeathScythe looks at the Maximal in disbelief. His eyes go to the
Maximal&#39;s
&gt; stump of an arm, where seconds before there appeared to be a fully
functional
&gt; limb. Looking back up to the captain&#39;s face, DeathScythe notices that the
&gt; knife in the Maximal&#39;s shoulder has turned into a small silver spoon.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;YOU SLAG! YOU TOOK IT!!!!!&quot; he screams, jumping at the Maximal and
swinging
&gt; the arm. &quot;DIE! DIE! DIE! DIE!&quot; he keeps yelling, whacking the Maximal with
&gt; the bot&#39;s own arm.
&gt; ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
&gt; &quot;Replication complete.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; DeathScythe opens his eyes. He was on his back, laying on cold ground.
Above
&gt; him was the night sky. DeathScythe turns his head, looking at a metal
plate
&gt; of the ship.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;AHHH!!&quot; he jumps up, ready for battle against the hellish spawn he saw in
&gt; the reflection. He blinks, realizing that the hellish spawn was himself.
&gt;
&gt; DeathScythe smiles, admiring his new beast mode in the mirror. Either the
&gt; ship was hit pretty bad, or this was one psycho planet. DeathScythe looked
&gt; like all the animals on earth put together. His hind legs were that of a
&gt; wolf, only much larger, so they could work together with his front legs,
&gt; looking almost like a gurrila&#39;s hands, but ending in two mismatched
hooves.
&gt; His tail was a snake&#39;s tail, ending with a scorpion stinger.
&gt;
&gt; DeathSythe back was covered by both fur, hide, and scales, different
patches
&gt; of covering for different spots. Out of the middle of his back stuck out
two
&gt; wings, in strange angles. From the angles of the wings, it was obvious
that
&gt; they were useless in flight, just there for apearence. In between the
wings,
&gt; a shark fin sticks out, leaning slightly to the left. His underbelly was
&gt; covered with scales, fur sticking through them. Out of his sides stuck
&gt; various fish fins, creating something like side teeth for the assassin.
&gt;
&gt; His snout was hideous. From the middle of what looked like a T-rex&#39;s face,
a
&gt; rhino horn stuck out. Where the snout would be there was a bump, a
seemingly
&gt; human nose emerging from it. Under that was another bump, the mouth gaping
&gt; its horrid collection of teeth, taken from various species on the planet.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;DeathScythe, ASSASSINATE!!!!&quot;
&gt;
&gt; DeathScythe transforms into robot mode, looking again at the plate. He was
&gt; almost as hideous as he was in beast mode. His wolf hind-legs served as
his
&gt; feet, an extra pair of arms coming out to serve as his robot arms, leaving
&gt; two hooves sticking out behind his back. Out of his shoulder stuck several
&gt; fish fins, the other one carrying the shark fin. His whole body was random
&gt; patches of different skins, hides, fur, and scales. Out of his back stuck
his
&gt; beast mode head, grinning its collection of teeth. His wings were folded
over
&gt; his back, providing a cape to hide his second head, making it look like a
&gt; hump on his back. His robot head remained unchanged, still the evil
mercyless
&gt; face of an assassin.
&gt;
&gt; DeathScythe smiles. He looked horrid. He looked like a freak. He could
pass
&gt; as something from the pit itself! He rather liked it.
&gt;
&gt; DeathScythe looks at the other bots near the ship, all of them dead. He
grins
&gt; evilly as he looks at the captain. &quot;Thought you could confuse me, eh?&quot;
&gt;
&gt; He walks over to the captain, kicking him before turning to disapear into
the
&gt; woods.
